parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails while driving
often without warning; the check engine light may come on; the vehicle may jerk violently or make a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Oil Leaks or Low Oil Pressure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure due to oil leaks or low oil pressure can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil light comes on; the engine makes a loud noise or knocks; the vehicle loses power or stalls; the oil dipstick is found to be bone dry.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold leaks or failure can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on; the vehicle stalls or loses power; coolant leaks from the intake manifold; the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates; the vehicle loses power or stalls; the transmission fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure or accidents.
symptoms: The coolant light comes on; the vehicle overheats; coolant leaks from the radiator or hoses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on; the vehicle stalls or loses power; the electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key falls out of the ignition while driving
the ignition switch locks up
the key will not turn or release out of the ignition
the vehicle stalls or will not start
the steering wheel locks
the vehicle's engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's power windows, lights, or other accessories to malfunction, leading to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: The power window switch burns out
the regulator is shorted out
the area around the switch is sticky
the headlights flicker or go dim
the service engine soon light comes on
the vehicle experiences loss of engine power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience or accidents.
symptoms: The starter fails and needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding sound
hesitation or failure to shift into gear
delayed engagement
RPM racing
and loss of reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Soft or spongy clutch pedal
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
delayed return of clutch pedal
and sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose shift lever and release button can cause the vehicle to shift into neutral or other gears unintentionally, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Loose shift lever
easy sliding of lever past gears
and unintended shifting into neutral or other gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the reverse gear can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding sound
hesitation or failure to shift into reverse
and loss of reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission leaks can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
grinding sound
and hesitation or failure to shift into gear.
